50%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margi=
n-bottom:0px;">As if Orozco=E2=80=99s output weren=E2=80=99t already diffic=
ult enough to categorize, the show
adds yet another element to complicate any taxonomy. The Jumex retrospectiv=
e is organized not <em>chronologically</em>, but rather in stratified layer=
s based on the artist=E2=80=99s own =E2=80=9Cgroupings of material objects =
in time and space.=E2=80=9D The top floor is =E2=80=9Cfloating, aerated and=
 streamlined matter.=E2=80=9D One flight below is =E2=80=9Cvegetal, an enta=
nglement of life-matter, ranging from the primordial through to the artific=
e of gardens.=E2=80=9D The ground floor is =E2=80=9Can aquarium but also =
=E2=80=A6 a ground of action, leading onto the
dry world of the terrace that is also a sculpture garden.=E2=80=9D Beneath =
all of this is a basement gallery that is meant to function as the =E2=80=
=9Ccompost, a composite of ideas and voices.=E2=80=9D In case you haven=E2=
=80=99t been paying attention, the intent here is to create an ecosystem of=
 air, earth, and water where Orozco=E2=80=99s ideas can circulate=E2=80=94o=
r the viewer can circulate within them.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bott=
om:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">If all of that is too abstract an=
d high-minded for you, the
simple beauty of Orozco=E2=80=99s objects makes it easy to jettison the lof=
ty concepts and simply enjoy the atavistic pleasures of his river stones ca=
rved with circles and lines, or his found objects arranged in forms that re=
flect his interest in geometry or have recursive geometric forms painted on=
 them.</p></div>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
